def Augmented_Dickey_Fuller_Test_func(series , column_name):
    print (f'Results of Dickey-Fuller Test for column: {column_name}')
    dftest = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    dfoutput = pd.Series(dftest[0:4], index=['Test Statistic','p-value','No Lags Used','Number of Observations Used'])
    for key,value in dftest[4].items():
       dfoutput['Critical Value (%s)'%key] = value
    print (dfoutput)
    if dftest[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion:====>")
        print("Reject the null hypothesis")
        print("Data is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion:====>")
        print("Fail to reject the null hypothesis")
        print("Data is non-stationary")

# check if data is stationary

def is_data_stationary( df_test, column ):
    print("column:", column)
    print("column:", column)
    adf_result = adfuller( df_test if column is None else df_test[column] )
    df_adf = pd.DataFrame( adf_result, index=['adf','pvalue', 'usedlag', 'numobs', 'criticalvals', 'infocritical'],
                           columns=['Value'])
    df_adf_critical = pd.DataFrame(adf_result[4] , index=['criticalval'])
    print(df_adf)
    print(df_adf_critical)
    print("Null Hypothesis: Time series is not stationary. That is time series has unit root.")
    print("Alternate Hypothesis: Time series is  stationary. That is time series has no unit root.")

    if df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0] < df_adf_critical['1%'].iloc[0]:
            print("Test statistics", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0],
                  'is lesser than critical value(1%)',
                  df_adf_critical['1%'].iloc[0])
    if df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0] < df_adf_critical['5%'].iloc[0]:
            print("Test statistics", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0],
                  'is lesser than critical value(5%)',
                  df_adf_critical['5%'].iloc[0])
    if df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0] < df_adf_critical['10%'].iloc[0]:
            print("Test statistics", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0],
                  'is lesser than critical value(10%)',
                  df_adf_critical['10%'].iloc[0])
    else:
        print("Test statistics", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0],
              'is greater than all critical value(10%)',
              df_adf_critical['10%'].iloc[0])    

    if df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'adf', 'Value'].iloc[0] < 0.05:
        print("p-value", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'pvalue', 'Value'].iloc[0] ,"is significant. Hence we reject null hypothesis")
        print("That is, Time series is stationary.")
    else:
        print("p-value", df_adf.loc[df_adf.index == 'pvalue', 'Value'].iloc[0] ,"is not significant. Hence we fail to reject null hypothesis")
        print("That is, Time series is NOT stationary.")
        

for column in list(df_store_1050_d.columns):
    is_data_stationary(df_store_1050_d, column)
    print("-"*50)

In [42]:
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen

def cointegration_test(df2): 
    res = coint_johansen(df2,-1,7)
    d = {'0.90':0, '0.95':1, '0.99':2}
    traces = res.lr1
    cvts = res.cvt[:, d[str(1-0.05)]]
    def adjust(val, length= 6): 
        return str(val).ljust(length)
    print('Column Name   >  Test Stat > C(95%)    =>   Signif  \n', '--'*20)
    for col, trace, cvt in zip(df2.columns, traces, cvts):
        print(adjust(col), '> ', adjust(round(trace,2), 9),
              ">", adjust(cvt, 8), ' =>  ' , trace > cvt)

    print(f'Searching order of p and q for : {name}')

                                start_p=1,

df_results = pd.DataFrame(columns=['p', 'q','RMSE Open','RMSE High','RMSE Low','RMSE Close'])
print('Grid Search Started')
#req_columns = ["Customers",'Open_1','Promotion_1']
start = timer()
for i in pq:
    if i[0]== 0 and i[2] ==0:
        pass
    else:
        print(f' Running for {i}')
        model = VARMAX(train[req_columns], order=(i[0],i[2])).fit( disp=False)
        result = model.forecast(steps = len(test))
        Custrmse = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(test['Customers'], result['Customers']))
        Openrmse = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(test['Open_1'], result['Open_1']))
        Promormse = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(test['Promotion_1'], result['Promotion_1']))
        df_results = df_results._append({'p': i[0], 
                                         'q': i[2],
                                        'RMSE Customers':Custrmse,
                                        'RMSE Open':Openrmse,
                                        'RMSE Promotion':Promormse }, 
                                       ignore_index=True)
end = timer()
print(f' Total time taken to complete grid search in seconds: {(end - start)}')
